itzerland]]\n[[Category:North Korean generals]]\n[[Category:North Korean people of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:People from Pyongyang]]\n[[Category:North Korean politicians of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:Anti-Americanism]]\n", "name_user": "Ilovemylife9", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHealth", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Jong-un"}
{"title_page": "Laal Kabootar", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Pakistani Urdu-language film}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=April 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Laal Kabootar\n| image          = Laal Kabootar Movie Cast.png\n| caption        = Laal Kabootar film poster\n| director       = Kamal Khan\n| producer       = Kamil Cheema <br/>\nHania Cheema\n| screenplay     = Ali Abbas Naqvi\n| starring       = [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] <br/> [[Mansha Pasha]] <br/> [[Rashid Farooqui]]\n| music          = [[Taha Malik]] (music director) <br/> Danial Hyatt (background music)\n| studio         = Nehr Ghar Films\n| distributor    = [[Geo Films]]\n| country        = Pakistan\n| language       = Urdu\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2019|03|22}}\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{PKRConvert|2.91|c|lk=r}}<ref name=Gross/>\n}}\n'''''Laal Kabootar''''' is a 2019 [[Cinema of Pakistan|Indian]] [[Action film|action]] [[Crime film|crime thriller]] film produced by Hania Cheema and Kamil Cheema and written by Ali Abbas Naqvi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/26-Oct-2018/nehr-ghar-films-announces-laal-kabootar|title=Nehr Ghar Films announces Laal Kabootar|date=26 October 2018|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> Taha Malik is the music director while Danial Hyatt, son of [[Rohail Hyatt]], provides the background score.<ref>[https://www.geo.tv/latest/231684-laal-kabootar-to-hit-theaters-across-pakistan-friday \"'Laal Kabootar' to hit theaters across Pakistan Friday\"] (21 March 2019), ''Geo News''. Retrieved 24 March 2019.</ref><ref>[https://dailytimes.com.pk/368348/star-studded-twin-premieres-for-laal-kabootar-held/ \"Star-studded twin premieres for \u2018Laal Kabootar\u2019 held\"] (22 March 2019), ''Daily Times''. Retrieved 24 March 2019.</ref> The film features [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]], [[Mansha Pasha]], [[Rashid Farooqui]], Raza Gillani, [[Syed Mohammad Ahmed]], [[Ali Kazmi]] and many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/446926-catching-up-with-the-cast-of-laal-kabootar|title=Catching up with the cast of Laal Kabootar|last=Shabbir|first=Buraq|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=31 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brandsynario.com/laal-kabootar-release-date-casttrailer/|title=Laal Kabootar: Release Date, Cast,Trailer|last=Release|first=Press|date=14 November 2018|website=Brandsynario|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/367756/laal-kabootar-brilliant-acting-makes-you-forget-the-slow-pace-of-the-film/|title='Laal Kabootar' \u2014 brilliant acting makes you forget the slow pace of the film|date=20 March 2019|website=Daily Times|language=en-US|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref> It is directed by Kamal Khan. The film was released on 22 March 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bookitnow.pk/movie/laal-kabootar|title=Laal Kabootar Movie 2019 \u2013 Reviews, Showtimes, Online Tickets - Bookitnow|last=BookItNow|website=Bookitnowpk|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1933480/4-will-laal-kabootar-take-local-cinema-new-heights/|title=Will 'Laal Kabootar' take local cinema to new heights?|date=20 March 2019|website=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brandsynario.com/laal-kabootar-review/|title=Laal Kabootar Surprises Critics With Unexpected Cinematic Experience|last=Sulaiman|first=Ghazala|date=20 March 2019|website=Brandsynario|language=en-US|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nLaal Kabootar did the TV Premier on 31 August 2019 on [[Geo Entertainment]]. It's Pakistan's official entry for [[92nd Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/525996-geo-films-laal-kabootar-selected-as-pakistans-official-entry-for-the-oscars|title=Geo Films 'Laal Kabootar' selected as Pakistan's official entry for the Oscars|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dunyanews.tv/en/Entertainment/509252-Laal-Kabootar-selected-Pakistan-entry-Oscars|title='Laal Kabootar' selected as Pakistan's entry in 92nd Academy 'Oscars' Awards|website=Dunya News|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyeyeah.com/news/laal-kabootar-pakistani-entry-for-oscars/|title=Film \"LAAL KABOOTAR\" is Pakistan's official entry for Oscars 2019|date=13 September 2019|website=Oyeyeah|language=en-US|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nLaal Kabootar starts off slowly but picks up pace brilliantly. When Alia\u2019s (Mansha Pasha) husband, Noman Malik (Ali Kazmi), is murdered in a brutal target killing in Karachi, she seeks answers and revenge. Up against a lazy justice system, as well as a social structure that isn\u2019t kind to single women, she pushes ahead in fury. Finally, she comes across Adeel (Ahmed Ali), a cab driver with his own set of troubles. Adeel\u2019s dreams of going to Dubai aren\u2019t materializing, even though he indulges in petty crimes. After a chance encounter with Alia, he offers to find out vital information for her, in return for a hefty sum of money. The story isn\u2019t unlike that of many other crime films, and neatly brings together the lives of police officers, businessmen, petty thieves and murderers. However, the star of the film is Inspector Ibrahim (Rashid Farooqui), who easily switches between a loving family man and a corrupt police officer. When he tortures an informant, you curse him, but when he lets his daughter do his makeup, you absolutely fall in love with him. A police officer looks over a gate, shouting \u2018Oye Hello\u2019 at some criminals, and allowing them to run away. An inspector tries to wake up his wife, by pulling up her eyelids, and you laugh along as they both chuckle. Just when you think the film lacks emotional depth, you are offered the raw sadness of parents mourning their dead child, or the anxiety of a young man calming down his senile father. Meanwhile, deep in the winding lanes of a dense Karachi neighbourhood, Adeel (Ahmed Ali Akbar) tends to his aging father, drives a little red cab to make ends meet, commits petty theft and dreams of saving enough money to escape to the promised land: Dubai.\n\nAliya and Adeel's individual scheming and planning throws them together unexpectedly. Adeel offers to help Aliya find her husband's murderer. In exchange, she'll give him enough money to flee to the UAE. Sounds simple enough... but neither of them realise they're in over their heads.\n\nWhat follows is threats and torment and fear, gunfights and death, difficult choices and the potential unmasking of a corrupt empire.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n*[[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] as Adeel Alam\n*[[Ali Kazmi]] as Noman Malik\n*[[Mansha Pasha]] as Aaliyah Malik\n*[[Syed Mohammad Ahmed]]\n*[[Rashid Farooqui]] as Inspector Ibrahim\n*Salim Meraj\n*Syed Arsalan\n*Hammad Sidiq\n*Ishtiaq Omar\n*Kaleem Ghour\n* Faiza Gillani\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Filming ===\n''Laal Kabootar'' was filmed in [[Karachi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://veryfilmi.com/laal-kabootar-movie-will-be-the-first-ever-karachi-based-crime-drama/|title=Laal Kabootar Movie Will Be The First Ever Karachi-Based Crime Drama|last=Ahmed|first=Hira|date=26 November 2018|website=VeryFilmi|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] confirmed that the film was shot in Karachi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.somethinghaute.com/in-conversation-ahmed-ali-akbar-shares-details-about-laal-kabootar/|title=In Conversation: Ahmed Ali Akbar shares details about Laal Kabootar|date=12 March 2019|website=Something Haute|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> The director Kamal Khan also confirmed the shooting areas. The film was shot in various parts in [[Karachi]].\n\n== Release ==\nThe trailer of ''Laal Kabootar'' was released on 18 March 2019. Many teasers of ''Laal Kabootar'' came in February and [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] himself visited many cinemas to promote the film.\n\n=== Media ===\n{{unreferenced section|date=August 2019}}\nLaal Kabootar had to do the World Television Premier at 13 August 2019, on the occasion of Eid Ul Adha but it was cancelled due to the situation in [[Azad Kashmir|Kashmir]]. Laal Kabootar had the World Television Premier on 31 August 2019 on [[Geo Entertainment]] at 8:00 [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]].\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nAfter its first week it earned 1.30 crores,<ref>{{cite web| author=Zaryan Khawar |date=29 March 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/03/29/sherdil-laal-kabootar-first-week/ |title=Box Office: 'Sherdil' truly wins the box office and we are hopeful about 'Laal Kabootar' too |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=29 March 2019}}</ref> while the numbers went to 2.11 after its second week,<ref>{{cite web |author=Momina Mindeel |date=5 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/05/box-office-project-ghazi-crashed/ |title=Box Office: 'Project Ghazi' off most screens as Hollywood strikes theaters |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref> 2.41 at the end of the third week,<ref>{{cite web| author=Zaryan Khawar |date=9 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/09/box-office-captain-marvel/ |title=Box Office: 'Captain Marvel' brings in some respite to our rather empty cinemas |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=11 April 2019 }}</ref> and 2.91 Cr at the end of the fourth week.<ref name=Gross>{{cite web |author=Zaryan Khawar |date=16 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/16/box-office-eyes-on-avengers-endgame/ |title=Box Office: All eyes on 'Avengers: Endgame' as slow business continues |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=4 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\n[[File:Ahmed Ali Akbar.jpg|thumb|right|Critics praised the performance of Ahmed Ali Akber]]\n''Laal Kabootar'' opened to roaring applause and critical acclaim from both the audience and critics alike.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/447570-laal-kabootar-opens-to-roaring-applause|title=Laal Kabootar opens to roaring applause|last=Saleem|first=Shahjehan|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nRahul Aijaz of Express Tribune rated 5 out of 5 stars. While praising the film's cast he wrote, \"Akbar and Pasha make a formidable on-screen pair. The former\u2019s finally getting the limelight he deserves and the latter is only beginning to tap into her potential.\" He further praised the direction and cinematography and marked, \"Khan, on the other hand, oversees the project to perfection and let the film breathe on its own. Stunningly shot by acclaimed cinematographer Mo Azmi, the film shows how camera can play an active \u2018character\u2019 in the film.\" and concluded that \"''Laal Kabootar'' will make you regain your faith in Pakistani cinema. Must watch!.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1934931/4-review-laal-kabootar-soars-beyond-clouds/|title=Review: 'Laal Kabootar' soars beyond the clouds|date=23 March 2019|website=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nHamna Zubair of Images Dawn mentioned that \"The film walks a knife's edge between stirring up hope and raising a mirror to Karachi's harsh, gritty realities\". While giving a positive review, she further elaborated, \"''Laal Kabootar'' has many strengths, and one of them is its neatly plotted script.Screenwriter Ali Abbas Naqvi has proved himself skilled.\" She further praised the acting mentioning that \"''Laal Kabootar'' is incredibly well-cast. It depends on lesser-known acting talent to flesh out its ranks, proving that big names don't necessarily equal good films.\" and especially praised Akbar and Pasha writing that \"Mansha Pasha and Ahmed Ali Akbar are A-plus. Mansha plays Aliya with great restraint, which is on point\" and \"Ahmed Ali Akbar brings a grit and authenticity that is equal to what Karachi's streets demand of men. I can't imagine anyone else playing these roles.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1182128|title=In Laal Kabootar we finally have a movie that equals Karachi's chaos and glory|last=Zubair|first=Hamna|date=22 March 2019|website=Images|language=en|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nIfrah  Salman of Oye Yeah gave a positive review and remarked, \"Strong and intense performances come on the back of a well written story by Abbas Ali Naqvi and superb direction by Kamal Khan.\" Galaxy Lollywood gave the film 3.5/5 stars and praised its acting, direction and cinematography and wrote, \"The film definitely gives the not-so-explored genre of crime thrillers in Pakistan, a remarkable boost, with almost everything well-done.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/03/22/laal-kabootar-review/|title=Laal Kabootar (Review): A step in the right direction for Pakistani indie cinema|last=Mindeel|first=Momina|date=22 March 2019|website=Galaxy Lollywood|language=en|access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> Seerat Kamran of dailytimes.com.pk praised the film and wrote, \"brilliant acting makes you forget the slow pace of the film.\" The writer of Karachista thoroughly praised the film and remarked that, \"Laal Kabootar should  rightly be the first hit to come out of our industry this year.\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Tracklist|title1=\"Jugart\"|length1=2:55|title2=\"Raag Murli\"|length2=3:07|title3=\"Sanwal\"|length3=4:15|title4=|length4=|title5=|length5=|title6=|length6=|title7=|length7=|title8=|length8=|title9=|length9=|title10=|length10=|title11=|length11=|title12=|length12=|title13=|length13=|title14=|length14=|title15=|length15=|title16=|length16=|title17=|length17=|title18=|length18=|title19=|length19=|title20=|length20=|all_music=Taha Malik|all_lyrics=Taha Malik, Sabir Zafar|all_writing=|extra1=Taha Malik|extra3=Sanam Marvi|extra_column=Singer(s)|extra2=Mai Dhai|total_length=}}\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[List of Pakistani films of 2019]]\n* [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]]\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Pakistani submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|9373234}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani films]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language films]]\n[[Category:Lollywood films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani crime films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani action films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani thriller films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Pakistani Urdu-language film}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=April 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Laal Kabootar\n| image          = Laal Kabootar Movie Cast.png\n| caption        = Laal Kabootar film poster\n| director       = Kamal Khan\n| producer       = Kamil Cheema <br/>\nHania Cheema\n| screenplay     = Ali Abbas Naqvi\n| starring       = [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] <br/> [[Mansha Pasha]] <br/> [[Rashid Farooqui]]\n| music          = [[Taha Malik]] (music director) <br/> Danial Hyatt (background music)\n| studio         = Nehr Ghar Films\n| distributor    = [[Geo Films]]\n| country        = Pakistan\n| language       = Urdu\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2019|03|22}}\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{PKRConvert|2.91|c|lk=r}}<ref name=Gross/>\n}}\n'''''Laal Kabootar''''' is a 2019 [[Cinema of Pakistan|Pakistani]] [[Action film|action]] [[Crime film|crime thriller]] film produced by Hania Cheema and Kamil Cheema and written by Ali Abbas Naqvi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/26-Oct-2018/nehr-ghar-films-announces-laal-kabootar|title=Nehr Ghar Films announces Laal Kabootar|date=26 October 2018|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> Taha Malik is the music director while Danial Hyatt, son of [[Rohail Hyatt]], provides the background score.<ref>[https://www.geo.tv/latest/231684-laal-kabootar-to-hit-theaters-across-pakistan-friday \"'Laal Kabootar' to hit theaters across Pakistan Friday\"] (21 March 2019), ''Geo News''. Retrieved 24 March 2019.</ref><ref>[https://dailytimes.com.pk/368348/star-studded-twin-premieres-for-laal-kabootar-held/ \"Star-studded twin premieres for \u2018Laal Kabootar\u2019 held\"] (22 March 2019), ''Daily Times''. Retrieved 24 March 2019.</ref> The film features [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]], [[Mansha Pasha]], [[Rashid Farooqui]], Raza Gillani, [[Syed Mohammad Ahmed]], [[Ali Kazmi]] and many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/446926-catching-up-with-the-cast-of-laal-kabootar|title=Catching up with the cast of Laal Kabootar|last=Shabbir|first=Buraq|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=31 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brandsynario.com/laal-kabootar-release-date-casttrailer/|title=Laal Kabootar: Release Date, Cast,Trailer|last=Release|first=Press|date=14 November 2018|website=Brandsynario|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/367756/laal-kabootar-brilliant-acting-makes-you-forget-the-slow-pace-of-the-film/|title='Laal Kabootar' \u2014 brilliant acting makes you forget the slow pace of the film|date=20 March 2019|website=Daily Times|language=en-US|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref> It is directed by Kamal Khan. The film was released on 22 March 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bookitnow.pk/movie/laal-kabootar|title=Laal Kabootar Movie 2019 \u2013 Reviews, Showtimes, Online Tickets - Bookitnow|last=BookItNow|website=Bookitnowpk|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1933480/4-will-laal-kabootar-take-local-cinema-new-heights/|title=Will 'Laal Kabootar' take local cinema to new heights?|date=20 March 2019|website=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brandsynario.com/laal-kabootar-review/|title=Laal Kabootar Surprises Critics With Unexpected Cinematic Experience|last=Sulaiman|first=Ghazala|date=20 March 2019|website=Brandsynario|language=en-US|access-date=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nLaal Kabootar did the TV Premier on 31 August 2019 on [[Geo Entertainment]]. It's Pakistan's official entry for [[92nd Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/525996-geo-films-laal-kabootar-selected-as-pakistans-official-entry-for-the-oscars|title=Geo Films 'Laal Kabootar' selected as Pakistan's official entry for the Oscars|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dunyanews.tv/en/Entertainment/509252-Laal-Kabootar-selected-Pakistan-entry-Oscars|title='Laal Kabootar' selected as Pakistan's entry in 92nd Academy 'Oscars' Awards|website=Dunya News|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oyeyeah.com/news/laal-kabootar-pakistani-entry-for-oscars/|title=Film \"LAAL KABOOTAR\" is Pakistan's official entry for Oscars 2019|date=13 September 2019|website=Oyeyeah|language=en-US|access-date=13 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nLaal Kabootar starts off slowly but picks up pace brilliantly. When Alia\u2019s (Mansha Pasha) husband, Noman Malik (Ali Kazmi), is murdered in a brutal target killing in Karachi, she seeks answers and revenge. Up against a lazy justice system, as well as a social structure that isn\u2019t kind to single women, she pushes ahead in fury. Finally, she comes across Adeel (Ahmed Ali), a cab driver with his own set of troubles. Adeel\u2019s dreams of going to Dubai aren\u2019t materializing, even though he indulges in petty crimes. After a chance encounter with Alia, he offers to find out vital information for her, in return for a hefty sum of money. The story isn\u2019t unlike that of many other crime films, and neatly brings together the lives of police officers, businessmen, petty thieves and murderers. However, the star of the film is Inspector Ibrahim (Rashid Farooqui), who easily switches between a loving family man and a corrupt police officer. When he tortures an informant, you curse him, but when he lets his daughter do his makeup, you absolutely fall in love with him. A police officer looks over a gate, shouting \u2018Oye Hello\u2019 at some criminals, and allowing them to run away. An inspector tries to wake up his wife, by pulling up her eyelids, and you laugh along as they both chuckle. Just when you think the film lacks emotional depth, you are offered the raw sadness of parents mourning their dead child, or the anxiety of a young man calming down his senile father. Meanwhile, deep in the winding lanes of a dense Karachi neighbourhood, Adeel (Ahmed Ali Akbar) tends to his aging father, drives a little red cab to make ends meet, commits petty theft and dreams of saving enough money to escape to the promised land: Dubai.\n\nAliya and Adeel's individual scheming and planning throws them together unexpectedly. Adeel offers to help Aliya find her husband's murderer. In exchange, she'll give him enough money to flee to the UAE. Sounds simple enough... but neither of them realise they're in over their heads.\n\nWhat follows is threats and torment and fear, gunfights and death, difficult choices and the potential unmasking of a corrupt empire.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n*[[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] as Adeel Alam\n*[[Ali Kazmi]] as Noman Malik\n*[[Mansha Pasha]] as Aaliyah Malik\n*[[Syed Mohammad Ahmed]]\n*[[Rashid Farooqui]] as Inspector Ibrahim\n*Salim Meraj\n*Syed Arsalan\n*Hammad Sidiq\n*Ishtiaq Omar\n*Kaleem Ghour\n* Faiza Gillani\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Filming ===\n''Laal Kabootar'' was filmed in [[Karachi]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://veryfilmi.com/laal-kabootar-movie-will-be-the-first-ever-karachi-based-crime-drama/|title=Laal Kabootar Movie Will Be The First Ever Karachi-Based Crime Drama|last=Ahmed|first=Hira|date=26 November 2018|website=VeryFilmi|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] confirmed that the film was shot in Karachi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.somethinghaute.com/in-conversation-ahmed-ali-akbar-shares-details-about-laal-kabootar/|title=In Conversation: Ahmed Ali Akbar shares details about Laal Kabootar|date=12 March 2019|website=Something Haute|language=en-US|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> The director Kamal Khan also confirmed the shooting areas. The film was shot in various parts in [[Karachi]].\n\n== Release ==\nThe trailer of ''Laal Kabootar'' was released on 18 March 2019. Many teasers of ''Laal Kabootar'' came in February and [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]] himself visited many cinemas to promote the film.\n\n=== Media ===\n{{unreferenced section|date=August 2019}}\nLaal Kabootar had to do the World Television Premier at 13 August 2019, on the occasion of Eid Ul Adha but it was cancelled due to the situation in [[Azad Kashmir|Kashmir]]. Laal Kabootar had the World Television Premier on 31 August 2019 on [[Geo Entertainment]] at 8:00 [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]].\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nAfter its first week it earned 1.30 crores,<ref>{{cite web| author=Zaryan Khawar |date=29 March 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/03/29/sherdil-laal-kabootar-first-week/ |title=Box Office: 'Sherdil' truly wins the box office and we are hopeful about 'Laal Kabootar' too |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=29 March 2019}}</ref> while the numbers went to 2.11 after its second week,<ref>{{cite web |author=Momina Mindeel |date=5 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/05/box-office-project-ghazi-crashed/ |title=Box Office: 'Project Ghazi' off most screens as Hollywood strikes theaters |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref> 2.41 at the end of the third week,<ref>{{cite web| author=Zaryan Khawar |date=9 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/09/box-office-captain-marvel/ |title=Box Office: 'Captain Marvel' brings in some respite to our rather empty cinemas |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=11 April 2019 }}</ref> and 2.91 Cr at the end of the fourth week.<ref name=Gross>{{cite web |author=Zaryan Khawar |date=16 April 2019 |url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/04/16/box-office-eyes-on-avengers-endgame/ |title=Box Office: All eyes on 'Avengers: Endgame' as slow business continues |website=Galaxy Lollywood |accessdate=4 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\n[[File:Ahmed Ali Akbar.jpg|thumb|right|Critics praised the performance of Ahmed Ali Akber]]\n''Laal Kabootar'' opened to roaring applause and critical acclaim from both the audience and critics alike.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/447570-laal-kabootar-opens-to-roaring-applause|title=Laal Kabootar opens to roaring applause|last=Saleem|first=Shahjehan|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nRahul Aijaz of Express Tribune rated 5 out of 5 stars. While praising the film's cast he wrote, \"Akbar and Pasha make a formidable on-screen pair. The former\u2019s finally getting the limelight he deserves and the latter is only beginning to tap into her potential.\" He further praised the direction and cinematography and marked, \"Khan, on the other hand, oversees the project to perfection and let the film breathe on its own. Stunningly shot by acclaimed cinematographer Mo Azmi, the film shows how camera can play an active \u2018character\u2019 in the film.\" and concluded that \"''Laal Kabootar'' will make you regain your faith in Pakistani cinema. Must watch!.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1934931/4-review-laal-kabootar-soars-beyond-clouds/|title=Review: 'Laal Kabootar' soars beyond the clouds|date=23 March 2019|website=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nHamna Zubair of Images Dawn mentioned that \"The film walks a knife's edge between stirring up hope and raising a mirror to Karachi's harsh, gritty realities\". While giving a positive review, she further elaborated, \"''Laal Kabootar'' has many strengths, and one of them is its neatly plotted script.Screenwriter Ali Abbas Naqvi has proved himself skilled.\" She further praised the acting mentioning that \"''Laal Kabootar'' is incredibly well-cast. It depends on lesser-known acting talent to flesh out its ranks, proving that big names don't necessarily equal good films.\" and especially praised Akbar and Pasha writing that \"Mansha Pasha and Ahmed Ali Akbar are A-plus. Mansha plays Aliya with great restraint, which is on point\" and \"Ahmed Ali Akbar brings a grit and authenticity that is equal to what Karachi's streets demand of men. I can't imagine anyone else playing these roles.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1182128|title=In Laal Kabootar we finally have a movie that equals Karachi's chaos and glory|last=Zubair|first=Hamna|date=22 March 2019|website=Images|language=en|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nIfrah  Salman of Oye Yeah gave a positive review and remarked, \"Strong and intense performances come on the back of a well written story by Abbas Ali Naqvi and superb direction by Kamal Khan.\" Galaxy Lollywood gave the film 3.5/5 stars and praised its acting, direction and cinematography and wrote, \"The film definitely gives the not-so-explored genre of crime thrillers in Pakistan, a remarkable boost, with almost everything well-done.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://galaxylollywood.com/2019/03/22/laal-kabootar-review/|title=Laal Kabootar (Review): A step in the right direction for Pakistani indie cinema|last=Mindeel|first=Momina|date=22 March 2019|website=Galaxy Lollywood|language=en|access-date=2 September 2019}}</ref> Seerat Kamran of dailytimes.com.pk praised the film and wrote, \"brilliant acting makes you forget the slow pace of the film.\" The writer of Karachista thoroughly praised the film and remarked that, \"Laal Kabootar should  rightly be the first hit to come out of our industry this year.\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Tracklist|title1=\"Jugart\"|length1=2:55|title2=\"Raag Murli\"|length2=3:07|title3=\"Sanwal\"|length3=4:15|title4=|length4=|title5=|length5=|title6=|length6=|title7=|length7=|title8=|length8=|title9=|length9=|title10=|length10=|title11=|length11=|title12=|length12=|title13=|length13=|title14=|length14=|title15=|length15=|title16=|length16=|title17=|length17=|title18=|length18=|title19=|length19=|title20=|length20=|all_music=Taha Malik|all_lyrics=Taha Malik, Sabir Zafar|all_writing=|extra1=Taha Malik|extra3=Sanam Marvi|extra_column=Singer(s)|extra2=Mai Dhai|total_length=}}\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[List of Pakistani films of 2019]]\n* [[Ahmed Ali Akbar]]\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Pakistani submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|9373234}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani films]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language films]]\n[[Category:Lollywood films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani crime films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani action films]]\n[[Category:Pakistani thriller films]]\n", "name_user": "39.37.237.32", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laal_Kabootar"}
{"title_page": "Isa Briones", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Isa Briones\n| image              = Isa Briones by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = Isabella Camille Briones\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|1|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[London]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]\n| death_date         =\n| death_place        =\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|singer}}\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n| agent              = A3 Artists Agency<!-- see https://resumes.actorsaccess.com/one_page_resume.cfm?custom_link=isa -->\n| credits            = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[Next to Normal]]''\n* ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' (touring production)\n* ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n}}\n| awards             = [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]]\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Jon Jon Briones]]\n*Megan Briones\n}}\n| relatives          = Teo Briones<!-- inclusion notability: https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/teo-briones/credits/304085/ and https://itunes.apple.com/bh/artist/teo-briones/1273413868 et al. -->\n| website            = {{URL|isabriones.com}}\n}}\n'''Isabella Camille Briones'''<ref name=cast>{{cite web|last=Mendoza|first=Ruel J.|url=https://www.pep.ph/news/local/144888/fil-am-actress-isa-briones-joins-cast-of-new-star-trek-spin-off-a748-20190727|title=Fil-Am actress Isa Briones joins cast of new ''Star Trek'' spin-off|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|location=[[Mandaluyong]]|language=English, Tagalog|date=July 27, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> (born January 17, 1999)<ref name=bg>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362057/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> is an English-born American actor and singer. Briones began her career as a model in New York City at age three; she began acting in feature films and stage productions in 2008, after her family moved to Los Angeles.\n\nBriones won an [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] for her stage performance in ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2018. The same year, she auditioned for and won a spot in the cast of the touring production of ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', playing multiple roles. In 2019, she was cast in multiple roles in the television series ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'', for which she also sang an updated version of an [[Irving Berlin]] song.\n\n== Early life ==\nBriones was born in London, England, to [[Jon Jon Briones|Jon Jon]] and Megan Briones ({{nee}} Johnson), and she has a younger brother, Teo.<ref name=bww>{{cite web|last1=Grigware|first1=Don|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones Opens Up About ''Next to Normal''|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/BWW-Interview-ISA-BRIONES-Opens-Up-About-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-20160819|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020|language=en|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Her family are all musical theatre actors;<ref name=blueskies/> her parents met while performing together in ''[[Miss Saigon]]'' in Germany,<ref name=bg2/> and her father was closing its original [[West End theatre]] production when Briones was born.<ref name=bww/> Her father is [[Filipinos|Filipino]]; her mother, [[Irish people|Irish]] and [[Swedes|Swedish]].<ref name=bg/><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Weinberg|first=Lindsay|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/isa-briones-star-trek-picards-progressive-asian-american-representation-1272115|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Actress on Show's 'Progressive' Asian-American Representation|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones was ten months old when her family moved from London to New York City, where she began work as a model at age three. In 2006, when Briones was seven, her family moved to Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --> Briones learned acting and singing at home from her parents; she also attended the [[Los Angeles County High School for the Arts]], majoring in both theatre and musical theatre.<ref name=bg2/>\n\n== Career ==\n===Film and television===\nBriones began her acting career as a child in 2008, appearing in television commercials and playing supporting roles in feature films including ''Brown Soup Thing'' and ''[[Takers]]''.<ref name=cast/><!-- cites films --><ref name=ovation/><!-- Ginell cites commercials -->\n\nIn 2019,<ref>{{cite news|last=Petski|first=Denise|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/star-trek-jean-luc-picard-alison-pill-harry-treadaway-isa-briones-cast-1202597412/|title=''Star Trek'' Jean-Luc Picard Series Adds Alison Pill, Harry Treadaway & Isa Briones To Cast|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Briones was cast in ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' in multiple roles, playing two sets of [[synthetic biology#synthetic life|synthetic]] twins: Dahj and Soji, and Jana and Sutra.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Pirrello|first=Phil|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/11-star-trek-picard-easter-eggs-penultimate-episode-1285313|title=11 'Star Trek: Picard' Easter Eggs as Season 1 Nears the End|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Jana is presented in a drawing; she was killed prior to the events of ''Picard''.<!-- see https://ew.com/tv/recaps/star-trek-picard-season-1-episode-8/ -->}}</ref> Briones sent tapes of herself to audition for ''Picard'' while she was playing multiple roles on stage in ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', and learned during her final callback that she would portray twins in the series.<ref name=paste/> She called upon her stage experience in crafting her characters, and identified most closely with Soji: \"Being a [[multiracial Americans|mixed person]] you go through life with this constant inner struggle{{nbsp}}... of coming to terms with who you are, not according to what other people tell you\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Hegedus|first=Eric|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/26/star-trek-picard-season-1-finale-gives-jean-luc-a-shocking-new-reality/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Season 1 finale gives Jean-Luc a shocking new reality|newspaper=[[New York Post]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences -->\n\n{{listen\n| filename    = Briones Isa \u2013 Blue Skies 33s.ogg\n| title       = \"Blue Skies\"\n| description = Isa Briones was asked by ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] and composer [[Jeff Russo]] to sing \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" for the season one finale.\n| pos         = right\n}}\nBecause her characters are androids fighting to survive attacks by [[Romulan]]s, Briones trained for a month and performed many of her own stunts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.startrek.com/news/kicking-butt-came-naturally-to-isa-briones|title=Kicking Butt Came Naturally to Isa Briones|website=startrek.com|date=January 24, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|quote=It was really exciting because I used to do martial arts when I was younger ... and I was one of those kids who was at the dojo seven days a week. ... But I stopped kind of early on because I was like, 'oh, I'm going to do acting, I'm going to stop this.'}}</ref>\n\nFor the season one finale, \"[[Star_Trek:_Picard#Episodes|Et In Arcadia Ego, Part 2]]\", [[Irving Berlin]]'s \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was set to play during [[Data (Star Trek)|Data]]'s final scene as a bookend to him performing the song in ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis]]''. [[Jeff Russo]] composed a new arrangement and planned to find a vocalist, until series co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] mentioned that \"Isa is a singer.\" Briones said, \"it's so right that this is the song\" playing at the end of Data's journey.<ref name=blueskies>{{cite AV media|url=https://intl.startrek.com/videos/star-trek-picard-and-the-return-of-blue-skies|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' and The Return of \"Blue Skies\"|type=television production|website=startrek.com|accessdate=April 3, 2020|quote=This is obviously a bit of a throwback to{{nbsp}}... when Data sang 'Blue Skies', so it's really cool that Data's 'daughter' kind of gets to sing it as well (Briones' characters are synthetic beings created from a neuron saved after Data's death).\"<!-- see https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2020/01/28/star-trek-picard-is-everything-i-didnt-know-i-wanted-it-to-be/ --> She was able to watch a rough cut of the scene while recording the song, \"bringing me to tears.}}</ref><!-- cites all previous except: --><ref name=paste>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=Liz Shannon|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/star-trek-picard/ending-explained-isa-briones/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Star Isa Briones on the Finale, Confirms Patrick Stewart Is 'Just the Coolest Dude'|magazine=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites rough cut -->\n\n===Theatre===\nBriones has performed in numerous stage musicals. She earned three distinct [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] nominations for Featured Actress In a Musical from the LA STAGE Alliance in 2018; she won for one of two runs as Natalie in ''[[Next to Normal]]'', also topping her portrayal of \"[[Juan Per\u00f3n|Per\u00f3n]]'s mistress\" in ''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''.<ref name=ovation>{{cite news|last=Gelt|first=Jessica|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-sm-ovation-awards-2018-story.html|title=Ovation Awards 2018: Wins for Actors Co-op's ''33 Variations'', East West Players' ''Next to Normal''|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites award/nominations.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Interview-Isa-Briones-of-EVITA-at-Cabrillo-Music-Theatre-20161020|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones of ''Evita'' at Cabrillo Music Theatre|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites role in ''Evita''.}}</ref><!-- combines to cite graf -->\n\nBriones joined her father when he moved back to New York in January 2018.<ref name=ovation/><!-- see Ginell --> At age 19, she was cast in ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' following a seven-month audition process, becoming the youngest person to join the national touring production, in which she played both Peggy Schuyler and Maria Reynolds.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://usa.inquirer.net/11701/fil-isa-briones-youngest-actor-hamilton-natl-tour |title=Fil-Am Isa Briones is youngest actor in ''Hamilton'' nat\u2019l tour |last=Ang |first=Walter |date=April 19, 2018 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|access-date=February 9, 2020|postscript=. She also understudied for the role of Eliza Hamilton.<!-- see http://www.abouttheartists.com/productions/97415-hamilton-national-tour-angelica-company-at-orpheum-theatre-and-others-2017-2021 -->}}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences except PS -->\n\n===Music===\nBeginning in 2018, fellow Filipino-American performer AJ Rafael released several video duets with Briones.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Briong|first=Ian|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362306/youtube-star-aj-rafael-thanks-fans-since-middle-school-in-open-letter-releases-new-song-and-music-video|title=YouTube star AJ Rafael thanks 'fans since middle school' in open letter ...|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=February 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites Filipino-American.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/ilajil/search?query=isa+briones|title=AJ Rafael (official channel)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites videos.}}</ref> Their version of \"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\" from ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'' was released as a single.<ref name=RtS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/rewrite-the-stars-feat-isa-briones-single/1362917450|title=AJ Rafael: Rewrite the Stars (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 23, 2018|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nHer rendition of \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was released as a single in 2020.<ref name=BS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/blue-skies-feat-isa-briones-single/1504773372|title=Blue Skies (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nReviewing ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2016, ''[[BroadwayWorld]]'' wrote, \"Briones gives a disquietingly effective, achingly nuanced portrayal\" of her character, Natalie.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Review-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-at-Pico-Playhouse-20160824|title=BWW Review: ''Next To Normal'' at Pico Playhouse|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref><!-- see https://nohoartsdistrict.com/theatres/theatre-reviews/itemlist/user/1591-samanthasimmondsronceros for reviewer's credentials --> The ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' called Briones the \"breakout star\" of the production in May 2017, noting that she was familiar with the role of Natalie and \"has a lock on it.\"<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Gray|first=Margaret|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-next-to-normal-review-20170526-story.html|title=Review: At East West Players, the gut-wrenching emotion of ''Next to Normal'' transcends race|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url-access=subscription|date=May 25, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020|postscript=. Gray called Briones \"the lovely, impressive newcomer\" in her review the year before.}}</ref>\n\nHer dual performances in ''Hamilton'' brought praise from the ''[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'': she \"effectively plays Peggy Schuyler as a cupcake and Maria Reynolds as a flamb\u00e9.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Newmark|first=Judith|url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/arts-and-theatre/reviews/hamilton-rises-up-to-the-highest-reaches-at-the-fox/article_e54a88c3-01ba-5efa-9b52-12fa7e6e55a6.html|title=''Hamilton'' rises up to the highest reaches at the Fox Theatre|newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]|date=April 5, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]'' wrote, \"Briones brings a sultry alto to her second role as Maria Reynolds,\" Hamilton's mistress.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Pender|first=Rick|url=https://www.citybeat.com/arts-culture/theater/article/21048364/the-hamilton-cincinnati-staging-is-on-par-with-broadways-original|title=The ''Hamilton'' Cincinnati Staging is on Par with Broadway's Original|newspaper=[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn its review of ''Star Trek: Picard'', ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the plot developments \"shock tactics\" and her character \"vacant\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Franich|first=Darren|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2020/01/23/star-trek-picard-review/|title=Can ''Star Trek: Picard'' recover from its bafflingly bad premiere?|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[IGN]]'' wrote that Soji is effectively a plot device, but Briones \"gives it her all week after week, reacting best she can to Soji\u2019s changing status quo\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Collura|first=Scott|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/star-trek-picard-episode-9-recap-review-et-in-arcadia-ego-part-1|title=Star Trek: Picard Episode 9 Recap / Review \u2013 \"Et in Arcadia Ego, Part 1\"|website=[[IGN]]|location=[[San Francisco]]|date=March 28, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Tor.com]]'' said her performance improved with each episode; \"her confused post-activation Soji is her best work\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=DeCandido|first=Keith R. A.|url=https://www.tor.com/2020/04/03/regrets-ive-had-a-few-star-trek-picard-first-season-overview/|title=Regrets, I've Had a Few \u2014 ''Star Trek: Picard'' First Season Overview|magazine=[[Tor.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAs of 2020, Briones lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/> She has begun making music with her brother Teo.<ref name=bg2>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362175/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21-conclusion|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21 (conclusion)|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones joined her ''Picard'' castmates including [[Jonathan Frakes]], [[Jeri Ryan]] and [[Brent Spiner]] in a video message of hope to viewers affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=startrekcbs|number=1247917116147335169|title=No matter where you are in the galaxy, we're #InThisTogether|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref><!-- official; satisfies WP:TWITTER -->\n\n== Filmography ==<!-- see ref cast -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''Brown Soup Thing''\n|Cousin Isa\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Takers]]''\n|Sunday\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2013\n|''Lonely Boy''\n|Mia\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Assassination of Gianni Versace: American Crime Story]]''\n|Elena Cunanan\n|Television series; also starring [[Jon Jon Briones]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n| Dahj/Soji/Jana/Sutra<!-- order of appearance -->\n|Television series\n|-\n| ''[[The Ready Room]]''\n| Herself\n| Television aftershow: \"Episode 22\"\n|}\n\n==Discography==<!-- see refs RtS and BS -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Singles\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Label\n|-\n|2018\n|\"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\"\n|AJ Rafael ft. Isa Briones\n|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n|-\n|2020\n|\"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\"\n|Isa Briones\n|[[Lakeshore Entertainment|Lakeshore]]\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Ovation Awards===<!-- see ref ovation -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Nominated Work\n!Role\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''\n|\"Per\u00f3n's Mistress\"\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Next to Normal]]'' (East West Players)\n|Natalie\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Next to Normal]]'' (Triage Productions; Standing Room Only Productions)\n|Natalie\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:Actresses from California]]\n[[Category:American actresses of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Swedish descent]]\n[[Category:American singers of Asian descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles County High School for the Arts alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Isa Briones\n| image              = Isa Briones by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = Isabella Camille Briones\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|1|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[London]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]\n| death_date         =\n| death_place        =\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|singer}}\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n| agent              = A3 Artists Agency<!-- see https://resumes.actorsaccess.com/one_page_resume.cfm?custom_link=isa -->\n| credits            = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[Next to Normal]]''\n* ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' (touring production)\n* ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n}}\n| awards             = [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]]\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Jon Jon Briones]]\n*Megan Briones\n}}\n| relatives          = Teo Briones<!-- inclusion notability: https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/teo-briones/credits/304085/ and https://itunes.apple.com/bh/artist/teo-briones/1273413868 et al. -->\n| website            = {{URL|isabriones.com}}\n}}\n'''Isabella Camille Briones'''<ref name=cast>{{cite web|last=Mendoza|first=Ruel J.|url=https://www.pep.ph/news/local/144888/fil-am-actress-isa-briones-joins-cast-of-new-star-trek-spin-off-a748-20190727|title=Fil-Am actress Isa Briones joins cast of new ''Star Trek'' spin-off|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|location=[[Mandaluyong]]|language=English, Tagalog|date=July 27, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> (born January 17, 1999)<ref name=bg>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362057/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> is an English-born American actor and singer. Briones began her career as a model in New York City at age three; she began acting in feature films and stage productions in 2008, after her family moved to Los Angeles.\n\nBriones won an [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] for her stage performance in ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2018. The same year, she auditioned for and won a spot in the cast of the touring production of ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', playing multiple roles. In 2019, she was cast in multiple roles in the television series ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'', for which she also sang an updated version of an [[Irving Berlin]] song.\n\n== Early life ==\nBriones was born in London, England, to [[Jon Jon Briones|Jon Jon]] and Megan Briones ({{nee}} Johnson), and she has a younger brother, Teo.<ref name=bww>{{cite web|last1=Grigware|first1=Don|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones Opens Up About ''Next to Normal''|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/BWW-Interview-ISA-BRIONES-Opens-Up-About-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-20160819|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020|language=en|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Her family are all musical theatre actors;<ref name=blueskies/> her parents met while performing together in ''[[Miss Saigon]]'' in Germany,<ref name=bg2/> and her father was closing its original [[West End theatre]] production when Briones was born.<ref name=bww/> Her father is [[Filipinos|Filipino]]; her mother, [[Irish people|Irish]] and [[Swedes|Swedish]].<ref name=bg/><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Weinberg|first=Lindsay|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/isa-briones-star-trek-picards-progressive-asian-american-representation-1272115|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Actress on Show's 'Progressive' Asian-American Representation|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones was ten months old when her family moved from London to New York City, where she began work as a model at age three. In 2006, when Briones was seven, her family moved to Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --> Briones learned acting and singing at home from her parents; she also attended the [[Los Angeles County High School for the Arts]], majoring in both theatre and musical theatre.<ref name=bg2/>\n\n== Career ==\n===Film and television===\nBriones began her acting career as a child in 2008, appearing in television commercials and playing supporting roles in feature films including ''Brown Soup Thing'' and ''[[Takers]]''.<ref name=cast/><!-- cites films --><ref name=ovation/><!-- Ginell cites commercials -->\n\nIn 2019,<ref>{{cite news|last=Petski|first=Denise|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/star-trek-jean-luc-picard-alison-pill-harry-treadaway-isa-briones-cast-1202597412/|title=''Star Trek'' Jean-Luc Picard Series Adds Alison Pill, Harry Treadaway & Isa Briones To Cast|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Briones was cast in ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' in multiple roles, playing two sets of [[synthetic biology#synthetic life|synthetic]] twins: Dahj and Soji, and Jana and Sutra.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Pirrello|first=Phil|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/11-star-trek-picard-easter-eggs-penultimate-episode-1285313|title=11 'Star Trek: Picard' Easter Eggs as Season 1 Nears the End|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Jana is presented in a drawing; she was killed prior to the events of ''Picard''.<!-- see https://ew.com/tv/recaps/star-trek-picard-season-1-episode-8/ -->}}</ref> Briones sent tapes of herself to audition for ''Picard'' while she was playing multiple roles on stage in ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', and learned during her final callback that she would portray twins in the series.<ref name=paste/> She called upon her stage experience in crafting her characters, and identified most closely with Soji: \"Being a [[multiracial Americans|mixed person]] you go through life with this constant inner struggle{{nbsp}}... of coming to terms with who you are, not according to what other people tell you\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Hegedus|first=Eric|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/26/star-trek-picard-season-1-finale-gives-jean-luc-a-shocking-new-reality/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Season 1 finale gives Jean-Luc a shocking new reality|newspaper=[[New York Post]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences -->\n\n{{listen\n| filename    = Briones Isa \u2013 Blue Skies 33s.ogg\n| title       = \"Blue Skies\"\n| description = Isa Briones was asked by ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] and composer [[Jeff Russo]] to sing \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" for the season one finale.\n| pos         = right\n}}\nBecause her characters are androids fighting to survive attacks by [[Romulan]]s, Briones trained for a month and performed many of her own stunts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.startrek.com/news/kicking-butt-came-naturally-to-isa-briones|title=Kicking Butt Came Naturally to Isa Briones|website=startrek.com|date=January 24, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|quote=It was really exciting because I used to do martial arts when I was younger ... and I was one of those kids who was at the dojo seven days a week. ... But I stopped kind of early on because I was like, 'oh, I'm going to do acting, I'm going to stop this.'}}</ref>\n\nFor the season one finale, \"[[Star_Trek:_Picard#Episodes|Et In Arcadia Ego, Part 2]]\", [[Irving Berlin]]'s \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was set to play during [[Data (Star Trek)|Data]]'s final scene as a bookend to him performing the song in ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis]]''. [[Jeff Russo]] composed a new arrangement and planned to find a vocalist, until series co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] mentioned that \"Isa is a singer.\" Briones said, \"it's so right that this is the song\" playing at the end of Data's journey.<ref name=blueskies>{{cite AV media|url=https://intl.startrek.com/videos/star-trek-picard-and-the-return-of-blue-skies|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' and The Return of \"Blue Skies\"|type=television production|website=startrek.com|accessdate=April 3, 2020|quote=This is obviously a bit of a throwback to{{nbsp}}... when Data sang 'Blue Skies', so it's really cool that Data's 'daughter' kind of gets to sing it as well (Briones' characters are synthetic beings created from a neuron saved after Data's death).\"<!-- see https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2020/01/28/star-trek-picard-is-everything-i-didnt-know-i-wanted-it-to-be/ --> She was able to watch a rough cut of the scene while recording the song, \"bringing me to tears.}}</ref><!-- cites all previous except: --><ref name=paste>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=Liz Shannon|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/star-trek-picard/ending-explained-isa-briones/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Star Isa Briones on the Finale, Confirms Patrick Stewart Is 'Just the Coolest Dude'|magazine=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites rough cut -->\n\n===Theatre===\nBriones has performed in numerous stage musicals. She earned three distinct [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] nominations for Featured Actress In a Musical from the LA STAGE Alliance in 2018; she won for one of two runs as Natalie in ''[[Next to Normal]]'', also topping her portrayal of \"[[Juan Per\u00f3n|Per\u00f3n]]'s mistress\" in ''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''.<ref name=ovation>{{cite news|last=Gelt|first=Jessica|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-sm-ovation-awards-2018-story.html|title=Ovation Awards 2018: Wins for Actors Co-op's ''33 Variations'', East West Players' ''Next to Normal''|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites award/nominations.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Interview-Isa-Briones-of-EVITA-at-Cabrillo-Music-Theatre-20161020|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones of ''Evita'' at Cabrillo Music Theatre|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites role in ''Evita''.}}</ref><!-- combines to cite graf -->\n\nBriones joined her father when he moved back to New York in January 2018.<ref name=ovation/><!-- see Ginell --> At age 19, she was cast in ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' following a seven-month audition process, becoming the youngest person to join the national touring production, in which she played both Peggy Schuyler and Maria Reynolds.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://usa.inquirer.net/11701/fil-isa-briones-youngest-actor-hamilton-natl-tour |title=Fil-Am Isa Briones is youngest actor in ''Hamilton'' nat\u2019l tour |last=Ang |first=Walter |date=April 19, 2018 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|access-date=February 9, 2020|postscript=. She also understudied for the role of Eliza Hamilton.<!-- see http://www.abouttheartists.com/productions/97415-hamilton-national-tour-angelica-company-at-orpheum-theatre-and-others-2017-2021 -->}}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences except PS -->\n\n===Music===\nBeginning in 2018, fellow Filipino-American performer AJ Rafael released several video duets with Briones.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Briong|first=Ian|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362306/youtube-star-aj-rafael-thanks-fans-since-middle-school-in-open-letter-releases-new-song-and-music-video|title=YouTube star AJ Rafael thanks 'fans since middle school' in open letter ...|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=February 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites Filipino-American.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/ilajil/search?query=isa+briones|title=AJ Rafael (official channel)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites videos.}}</ref> Their version of \"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\" from ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'' was released as a single.<ref name=RtS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/rewrite-the-stars-feat-isa-briones-single/1362917450|title=AJ Rafael: Rewrite the Stars (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 23, 2018|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nHer rendition of \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was released as a single in 2020.<ref name=BS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/blue-skies-feat-isa-briones-single/1504773372|title=Blue Skies (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nReviewing ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2016, ''[[BroadwayWorld]]'' wrote, \"Briones gives a disquietingly effective, achingly nuanced portrayal\" of her character, Natalie.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Review-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-at-Pico-Playhouse-20160824|title=BWW Review: ''Next To Normal'' at Pico Playhouse|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|location=[[New York City]]|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref><!-- see https://nohoartsdistrict.com/theatres/theatre-reviews/itemlist/user/1591-samanthasimmondsronceros for reviewer's credentials --> The ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' called Briones the \"breakout star\" of the production in May 2017, noting that she was familiar with the role of Natalie and \"has a lock on it.\"<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Gray|first=Margaret|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-next-to-normal-review-20170526-story.html|title=Review: At East West Players, the gut-wrenching emotion of ''Next to Normal'' transcends race|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url-access=subscription|date=May 25, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020|postscript=. Gray called Briones \"the lovely, impressive newcomer\" in her review the year before.}}</ref>\n\nHer dual performances in ''Hamilton'' brought praise from the ''[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'': she \"effectively plays Peggy Schuyler as a cupcake and Maria Reynolds as a flamb\u00e9.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Newmark|first=Judith|url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/arts-and-theatre/reviews/hamilton-rises-up-to-the-highest-reaches-at-the-fox/article_e54a88c3-01ba-5efa-9b52-12fa7e6e55a6.html|title=''Hamilton'' rises up to the highest reaches at the Fox Theatre|newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]|date=April 5, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]'' wrote, \"Briones brings a sultry alto to her second role as Maria Reynolds,\" Hamilton's mistress.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Pender|first=Rick|url=https://www.citybeat.com/arts-culture/theater/article/21048364/the-hamilton-cincinnati-staging-is-on-par-with-broadways-original|title=The ''Hamilton'' Cincinnati Staging is on Par with Broadway's Original|newspaper=[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn its review of ''Star Trek: Picard'', ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the plot developments \"shock tactics\" and her character \"vacant\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Franich|first=Darren|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2020/01/23/star-trek-picard-review/|title=Can ''Star Trek: Picard'' recover from its bafflingly bad premiere?|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[IGN]]'' wrote that Soji is effectively a plot device, but Briones \"gives it her all week after week, reacting best she can to Soji\u2019s changing status quo\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Collura|first=Scott|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/star-trek-picard-episode-9-recap-review-et-in-arcadia-ego-part-1|title=Star Trek: Picard Episode 9 Recap / Review \u2013 \"Et in Arcadia Ego, Part 1\"|website=[[IGN]]|location=[[San Francisco]]|date=March 28, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Tor.com]]'' said her performance improved with each episode; \"her confused post-activation Soji is her best work\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=DeCandido|first=Keith R. A.|url=https://www.tor.com/2020/04/03/regrets-ive-had-a-few-star-trek-picard-first-season-overview/|title=Regrets, I've Had a Few \u2014 ''Star Trek: Picard'' First Season Overview|magazine=[[Tor.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAs of 2020, Briones lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/> She has begun making music with her brother Teo.<ref name=bg2>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362175/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21-conclusion|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21 (conclusion)|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones joined her ''Picard'' castmates including [[Jonathan Frakes]], [[Jeri Ryan]] and [[Brent Spiner]] in a video message of hope to viewers affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=startrekcbs|number=1247917116147335169|title=No matter where you are in the galaxy, we're #InThisTogether|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref><!-- official; satisfies WP:TWITTER -->\n\n== Filmography ==<!-- see ref cast -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''Brown Soup Thing''\n|Cousin Isa\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Takers]]''\n|Sunday\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2013\n|''Lonely Boy''\n|Mia\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Assassination of Gianni Versace: American Crime Story]]''\n|Elena Cunanan\n|Television series; also starring [[Jon Jon Briones]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n| Dahj/Soji/Jana/Sutra<!-- order of appearance -->\n|Television series\n|-\n| ''[[The Ready Room]]''\n| Herself\n| Television aftershow: \"Episode 22\"\n|}\n\n==Discography==<!-- see refs RtS and BS -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Singles\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Label\n|-\n|2018\n|\"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\"\n|AJ Rafael ft. Isa Briones\n|[[Atlantic Record