{"title_page": "John Newton (epidemiologist)", "text_new": "'''Professor John Newton''' FRCP FFPH FRSPH is a British [[epidemiologist]] and public health expert. He is the leader of the UK Government's COVID-19 testing programme.\n\n==Career==\nProfessor Newton was an academic epidemiologist at the [[University of Oxford]], and the founding Chief Executive of the charity [[UK Biobank]]. He also served as Director of Research at Oxford's [[John Radcliffe Hospital]] and at [[University Hospital Southampton NHS Foundation Trust|University Hospital Southampton]]. He was appointed Honorary Professor of Public Health and Epidemiology in the Centre for Epidemiology at the [[University of Manchester]] in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |title=Professor John Newton |url=http://www.festivalofpublichealth.co.uk/keynotespeakers/pastkeynotespeakers/professorjohnnewton/ |website=International Festival of Public Health |publisher=University of Manchester}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005 he led work for the UK [[Department of Health]] on a national public health information and intelligence strategy. He was appointed as Regional Director of Public Health for [[NHS South Central]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |title=Prof John Newton |url=https://www.e-cigarette-summit.com/speaker/prof-john-newton/ |website=E-cigarette Summit 2019 |publisher=Royal Society}}</ref>\n\nProfessor Newton was appointed as Director of Health Improvement for [[Public Health England]] on 12 October 2012.<ref>{{cite web |title=Director of Health Improvement Professor John Newton |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/people/john-newton |website=GOV.UK}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, he was announced as national coordinator of the UK Government's coronavirus testing programme.\n\n==Other roles==\nProfessor Newton chairs the [[World Health Organisation]]\u2019s European Burden of Disease Network and led England's contribution to the Global Burden of Disease project, a study into the impacts of diseases on the world.\n\nHe is Vice President of the Faculty of Public Health (FPH) <ref>{{cite web |title=About the Faculty of Public Health |url=https://www.fph.org.uk/about-fph/ |website=Faculty of Public Health}}</ref> and a director of Health Data Insight CIC.<ref>{{cite web |title=About Health Data Insight |url=https://healthdatainsight.org.uk/about-hdi/ |website=Health Data Insight CIC}}</ref> He is a fellow of the Royal College of Physicians of London (FRCP) and a fellow of the Royal Society for Public Health (FRSPH).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Newton, John}}\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians]]\n", "text_old": "'''Professor John Newton''' FRCP FFPH FRSPH is a British [[epidemiologist]] and public health expert. He is the leader of the UK Government\u2019s COVID-19 testing programme. \n\n==Career==\nProfessor Newton was an academic epidemiologist at the [[University of Oxford]], and the founding Chief Executive of the charity [[UK Biobank]]. He also served as Director of Research at Oxford\u2019s [[John Radcliffe Hospital]] and at [[University Hospital Southampton NHS Foundation Trust|University Hospital Southampton]]. He was appointed Honorary Professor of Public Health and Epidemiology in the Centre for Epidemiology at the [[University of Manchester]] in 2004. <ref>{{cite web |title=Professor John Newton |url=http://www.festivalofpublichealth.co.uk/keynotespeakers/pastkeynotespeakers/professorjohnnewton/ |website=International Festival of Public Health |publisher=University of Manchester}}</ref>\n\nIn 2005 he led work for the UK [[Department of Health]] on a national public health information and intelligence strategy. He was appointed as Regional Director of Public Health for [[NHS South Central]] in 2007. <ref>{{cite web |title=Prof John Newton |url=https://www.e-cigarette-summit.com/speaker/prof-john-newton/ |website=E-cigarette Summit 2019 |publisher=Royal Society}}</ref>\n\nProfessor Newton was appointed as Director of Health Improvement for [[Public Health England]] on 12 October 2012. <ref>{{cite web |title=Director of Health Improvement Professor John Newton |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/people/john-newton |website=GOV.UK}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, he was announced as national coordinator of the UK Government\u2019s coronavirus testing programme.\n\n==Other roles==\nProfessor Newton chairs the [[World Health Organisation]]\u2019s European Burden of Disease Network and led England's contribution to the Global Burden of Disease project, a study into the impacts of diseases on the world. \n\nHe is Vice President of the Faculty of Public Health (FPH) <ref>{{cite web |title=About the Faculty of Public Health |url=https://www.fph.org.uk/about-fph/ |website=Faculty of Public Health}}</ref> and a director of Health Data Insight CIC. <ref>{{cite web |title=About Health Data Insight |url=https://healthdatainsight.org.uk/about-hdi/ |website=Health Data Insight CIC}}</ref> He is a fellow of the Royal College of Physicians of London (FRCP) and a fellow of the Royal Society for Public Health (FRSPH). \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Newton, John}}\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal College of Physicians]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's (3)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Newton_(epidemiologist)"}
